ESPRESSO INSTRUCTIONS

Prerequisites: 
- On Device: turn of Window Animation Scale, Transition Animation Scale, and Animator Duration Scale
- Install Latest Android Support Repository

1. Open app/build.gradle and add these lines inside dependencies:

androidTestCompile 'com/android.support.test.espresso:espresso-core:2.2.2'
androidTestCompile 'com.android.support.test:runner:0.5'

2. Set instrumentation runner. Add following line in android.defaultConfig:

testInstrumentationRunner "android.support.test.runner.AndroidJUnitRunner"

3. Open Run -> Edit Configuration
Choose module and add instrumentation runner: android.support.test.runner.AndroidJUnitRunner

4. Run tests through studio or command line using ./gradlew connectedAndroidTest


Helpful Links:

UI Testing with Espresso://guides.codepath.com/android/UI-Testing-with-Espresso

